content: I'd like to help make progress on caching for doc.rust-lang.org (https://github.com/rust-lang/simpleinfra/issues/62), and I figured I'd take a look at the code that uploads to (presumably) S3, since that's a likely place to add it. But I don't see code to upload rustdocs in the simpleinfra repo (https://github.com/rust-lang/simpleinfra/). Should I be looking somewhere else?
I'm not sure, sorry. Maybe ask in #t-infra ?
I remember modifying this a while ago but I don't remember what repo it was in
Oh here we go, this looks right @jsha https://github.com/rust-lang/simpleinfra/blob/master/terraform/releases/impl/lambdas/doc-router/index.js
Err well https://github.com/rust-lang/simpleinfra/blob/a52fd8279d6b43d60b1c718903a88e914020be94/terraform/releases/impl/lambdas/static-router/index.js#L19 is probably closer. T-infra would know more.
